('4711', '4', 'Place the fillets, skin sides down, in a shallow roasting pan coated with cooking spray. cook at 500 for 13 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4711', '5', 'Heat the oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat.'),
('4711', '6', 'Add garlic, salt, and one package of spinach. saut 1 minute or until spinach wilts.'),
('4711', '7', 'Add remaining spinach, and cook 2 minutes or until the spinach wilts, stirring frequently.'),
('4711', '8', 'Remove from heat. toss with rice vinegar. Arrange 2/3 cup spinach mixture on each of 4 plates. add 1 salmon fillet.'),
('4711', '9', 'Garnish with onions, if desired.'),
('4712', '1', 'Place first 4 ingredients in a blender. process until smooth.'),
('4712', '2', 'Pour into a large zip-top plastic bag.'),
('4712', '3', 'Add salmon, and seal and marinate in refrigerator 1 hour, turning bag occasionally.'),
('4712', '4', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('4712', '5', 'Remove salmon from bag, discarding marinade.'),
('4712', '6', 'Place salmon on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. broil 8 minutes. Turn, and broil an additional 4 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4712', '7', 'Serve with lime wedges.'),
('4713', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('4713', '2', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.'),
('4713', '3', 'Combine 2 tablespoons sugar mixture and squash. toss gently. Arrange squash in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Arrange salmon on top of squash. brush with mustard. Sprinkle fish with remaining sugar mixture.'),
('4713', '4', 'Bake at 450 for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4713', '5', 'Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.'),
('4714', '1', 'Combine yogurt, dill, oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Cover and chill until used.'),
('4714', '2', 'Heat grill to medium-high (about 450).'),
('4715', '1', 'Combine the first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl. stir in 1/4 teaspoon salt.'),
('4715', '2', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and black pepper over fish.'),
('4715', '3', 'Add fish to pan. cook 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4715', '4', 'Place 1 fillet in each of 4 shallow bowls, and top each serving with 1/2 cup cucumber salad and 1 teaspoon peanuts.'),
('4716', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('4716', '2', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a large zip-top plastic bag.'),
('4716', '3', 'Add fish to bag. seal. Refrigerate 10 minutes, turning bag once.'),
('4716', '4', 'Remove fish from bag, reserving marinade.'),
('4716', '5', 'Place marinade in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave at HIGH 1 minute.'),
('4716', '6', 'Heat a large ovenproof nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle fish evenly with salt and pepper. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('4716', '7', 'Add fish to pan. cook 3 minutes. Turn fish over.'),
('4716', '8', 'Brush marinade evenly over fish. Broil 3 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4717', '1', 'Heat oven to 40'),
('4717', '2', 'Combine first 8 ingredients in a shallow dish. Sprinkle fillets with salt. dredge fillets in spice mixture.'),
('4717', '3', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('4717', '4', 'Add fillets, skin sides up. cook 5 minutes or until bottoms are golden. Turn fillets over. Wrap handle of skillet with foil. bake at 400 for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
