('4717', '6', 'Serve with yogurt and lemon wedges.'),
('4718', '1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Cover and refrigerate.'),
('4718', '2', 'Combine juice, oil, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and garlic, stirring with a whisk.'),
('4718', '3', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat. Sprinkle salmon with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('4718', '4', 'Add fish to pan. cook 9 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, turning once.'),
('4718', '5', 'Combine arugula mixture and juice mixture. toss well to coat.'),
('4718', '6', 'Place 1/2 cup herb salad on each of 6 plates. top each serving with 1 fillet.'),
('4718', '7', 'Serve with lemon wedges.'),
('4719', '1', 'Soak mushrooms in hot water 20 minutes or until soft. drain and cut into thin strips.'),
('4719', '2', 'Cut 3 (3/4-inch) deep lengthwise slits in each fillet.'),
('4719', '3', 'Combine cornstarch, salt, and pepper. sprinkle over fish.'),
('4719', '4', 'Let stand 10 minutes. Stuff mushroom strips and green onions into slits.'),
('4719', '5', 'Place fish in a 9-inch pie plate.'),
('4719', '6', 'Combine sake and the remaining ingredients. pour over fish.'),
('4719', '7', 'Place a bamboo steamer basket in a large wok, and add water to wok to a depth of 1 1/2 inches below basket. Bring the water to a boil.'),
('4719', '8', 'Place pie plate in bottom of steamer basket. cover and cook 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4719', '9', 'Wine note: In this dish, the sweet earthiness of the mushrooms and black bean sauce as well as the flavor of the salmon form a perfect counterpoint to the earthy flavors and silky texture of a good pinot noir. Try Sebastiani pinot noir 2002 (Russian River Valley, California), $23, with its forestlike aromas of earth, dried leaves, and underbrush, and its seductive flavors of dried cherries, mocha, and vanilla. -Karen MacNeil'),
('4720', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a large zip-top plastic bag. add fish. Seal and marinate in refrigerator 20 minutes, turning once.'),
('4720', '2', 'Prepare broiler.'),
('4720', '3', 'Remove fish from bag, reserving marinade.'),
('4720', '4', 'Place fish, skin sides down, on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. sprinkle with salt and pepper. Broil 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4720', '5', 'Bring reserved marinade to a boil in a small saucepan. Reduce heat, and simmer 3 minutes.'),
('4720', '6', 'Serve sauce with fish.'),
('4721', '1', 'To prepare sauce, combine first 10 ingredients in a food processor. process until smooth.'),
('4721', '2', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('4721', '3', 'To prepare fish, sprinkle fish with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('4721', '4', 'Place fish on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. broil 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4721', '5', 'Serve fish with sorrel sauce.'),
('4722', '1', 'Heat 1 1/2 tsp. oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('4722', '2', 'Add pumpkin seeds. saut until beginning to brown and pop, about 2 minutes.'),
('4722', '3', 'Transfer seeds to paper towels to drain. let cool. Reserve skillet. Pulse 6 Tbsp. pumpkin seeds, cilantro, coriander seeds, and garlic in a food processor until coarsely chopped. With machine running, gradually add 1 Tbsp. lime juice, 1/4 cup oil, then 1/4 cup water, blending until coarse pure forms. Season pesto to taste with salt, pepper, and more lime juice, if desired.'),
('4722', '4', 'Heat remaining 1 tsp. oil in reserved skillet over medium heat. Season salmon fillets with salt and pepper.'),
('4722', '5', 'Add to skillet and cook until just opaque in center, 34 minutes per side.'),
('4722', '6', 'Place fillets on plates. Spoon pesto over.'),
('4722', '7', 'Garnish with remaining pumpkin seeds.'),
('4722', '8', 'Serve with lime wedges.'),
('4723', '1', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('4723', '2', 'Sprinkle salmon fillets with salt and pepper.'),
('4723', '3', 'Place the fillets, skin sides up, in a large skillet or small roasting pan. Spoon chopped tomato around fillets, and drizzle fillets with soy sauce. Wrap handle of skillet with foil, and bake the fillets at 425 for 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4723', '4', 'Remove skin from fillets, and discard skin.'),
('4723', '5', 'Remove fillets from pan, and keep warm.'),
('4723', '6', 'Add the chopped tarragon and mustard to tomato, stirring well. Spoon tomato mixture over fillets.'),
('4723', '7', 'Garnish with tarragon sprigs, if desired.'),
('4724', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('4724', '2', 'To prepare fish, combine the first 6 ingredients in a small bowl, and brush evenly over fish. Arrange fish on a foil-lined baking sheet. broil for 8 minutes or until desired degree of doneness. Sprinkle with sesame seeds.'),
('4724', '3', 'To prepare spinach, while fish broils, heat sesame oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('4724', '4', 'Add garlic and spinach to skillet. cook 30 seconds or until spinach just begins to wilt, tossing mixture constantly. Stir in 2 teaspoons soy sauce.'),
('4725', '1', 'To prepare rice, bring 2 cups water to a boil in a small saucepan. Stir in rice and 1/4 teaspoon salt. cover, reduce heat, and cook for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.'),
('4725', '2', 'Remove from heat. stir in parsley and cashews. Keep warm.'),
('4725', '3', 'To prepare salmon, preheat broiler.'),
('4725', '4', 'Combine ginger and the next 5 ingredients (through pepper). Rub spice mixture evenly over salmon.'),
('4725', '5', 'Place fillets on a broiler pan or baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Cover with foil. broil 7 minutes.'),
('4725', '6', 'Remove foil. broil an additional 4 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4725', '7', 'Serve salmon with rice.'),
('4726', '1', 'Heat oven to 40'),
('4726', '2', 'Combine first 8 ingredients in a shallow dish. Sprinkle fillets with salt. dredge fillets in spice mixture.'),
('4726', '3', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('4726', '4', 'Add fillets, skin sides up. cook 5 minutes or until bottoms are golden. Turn fillets over. Wrap handle of skillet with foil. bake at 400 for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4726', '5', 'Remove skin from fillets. discard skin.'),
('4726', '6', 'Serve with yogurt and lemon wedges.'),
('4727', '1', 'Zest lemons to yield 2 tbsp. zest. Sprinkle salmon fillets with 1 1/2 tbsp. zest (set remaining zest and whole lemons aside) and 1 1/2 tbsp. dill, dividing evenly among fillets and patting to adhere. Wrap fillets in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours and up to overnight.'),
('4727', '2', 'Slice cucumber paper-thin on a mandoline or other handheld slicer.'),
('4727', '3', 'Cut onions in half. In a bowl, whisk together vinegar, sugar, and 1/2 tsp. salt.'),
('4727', '4', 'Add cucumber, onions, remaining lemon zest and dill, and toss gently to coat. Taste and adjust seasonings, if necessary.'),
('4727', '5', 'Prepare a gas or charcoal grill for indirect heat. If using a gas grill, turn all burners to high and close lid. When the temperature inside the grill reaches 400, lift lid and turn off one of the burners, creating the indirect-heat area. If using a charcoal grill, light 50 to 60 briquets and let burn until just covered with ash, 20 to 30 minutes. Mound them to one side, leaving a cleared area for indirect cooking.'),
('4727', '6', 'Fold two 12- by 18-in. pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil in half widthwise to form rectangles. Using the tip of a small knife, make holes in rectangles about 2 in. apart and widen each hole to the size of a dime. Grease foil with olive oil. set over direct heat for 2 minutes.'),
('4727', '7', 'Brush salmon skins with oil. Set 2 fillets, skin side down, on each foil rectangle. Cover grill (if using charcoal, open vents on lid) and cook fish until skin is light brown and really sizzling, 5 to 6 minutes. Using tongs, slide foil to indirect heat, cover, and cook until all but top 1/4 in. is cooked, 3 to 8 minutes. Slide fish back over direct heat, cover, and cook until fish is cooked through (cut to test) and skin is browned and crisp, about 3 minutes.'),
('4727', '8', 'Transfer foil with salmon to a rimless baking sheet and, sliding an offset cake spatula or other thin spatula between salmon skin and foil, very gently free fish from foil. Season each fillet with salt and a few drops of juice from a remaining lemon.'),
('4727', '9', 'Serve with cucumber salad.'),
('4728', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('4728', '2', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in a small bowl. stir with a whisk.'),
('4728', '3', 'Place salmon on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. brush with half of honey mixture. Broil 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, basting frequently with remaining honey mixture.'),
('4729', '1', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('4729', '2', 'Combine apple jelly, chives, horseradish, vinegar, and 1/4 teaspoon salt, stirring well with a whisk.'),
('4729', '3', 'Sprinkle salmon with 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.'),
('4729', '4', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('4729', '5', 'Add salmon, and cook 3 minutes. Turn salmon over. brush with half of apple mixture. Wrap handle of skillet with foil. bake at 350 for 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4729', '6', 'Brush with remaining apple mixture.'),
('4731', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan. bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer, uncovered, until reduced to 3/4 cup (about 20 minutes). Discard bay leaf.'),
('4731', '2', 'Combine milk and cornstarch, stirring with a whisk.'),
('4731', '3', 'Add to broth mixture. bring to a boil. Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in watercress. cook for 30 seconds. Keep warm.Arrange the salmon fillets in a single layer in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish, and sprinkle with lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Cover with plastic wrap, and vent. Microwave at high 4 1/2 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('4731', '4', 'Place 1 fillet on each of 4 plates. top each serving with 1/4 cup sauce.'),
('4731', '5', 'Garnish with watercress sprigs and lemon wedges, if desired.'),
('4733', '1', 'In a nonstick pan or griddle over medium-high heat add salmon and cook for about 4 minutes per side, flipping with a spatula. While the salmon is cooking, to a large cold skillet, add 2 tablespoons oil and garlic, then, turn pan on to protect garlic from burning.'),
('4733', '2', 'Add sliced mushrooms, and bok choy stalks, stirring constantly for 1 minute. Cover pan and cook for 5 minutes.'),
('4733', '3', 'Remove the lid and add the bok choy leaves, soy sauce, sesame oil, and continue to cook for another 2 to 3 minutes or until the leaves have wilted.'),
('4733', '4', 'Pile the mushrooms and greens on a plate with the salmon. Season with salt and pepper and serve immediately.'),
('4734', '1', 'Season salmon with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper. Set aside.Peel cucumber and cut into thin strips, proceed to finely chop.Toss into a bowl along with chopped onion, cilantro, mint and serrano chile.'),
('4734', '2', 'Add oil, lime juice, salt and pepper. Toss to coat and refrigerate until ready to serve.I used a (water soaked) hickory board to grill my salmon fillet. If you are putting the salmon directly on the grill, oil the skin and cook skin side down with lid closed. You don''t have to worry about the added oil since you are not eating the skin anyway. As for cooking times, it depends on how thick your fish is. A general rule is 10 minutes per 1" of thickness. See Notes section for a great grilling chart guide and link!'),
('4734', '3', 'Serve and Enjoy!'),
('4735', '1', 'Place salt and fish in a large zip-top plastic bag. shake bag to coat fish evenly. Chill 8 hours or overnight.'),
('4735', '2', 'Remove fish from bag. rinse well. Soak fish in ice water 2 hours, changing water every 30 minutes.'),
('4735', '3', 'Drain well. Pat fish dry with paper towels. Dice fish. place in a large bowl. Set aside.'),
('4735', '4', 'Soak white onion in ice water 15 minutes.'),
('4735', '5', 'Drain well.'),
('4735', '6', 'Add diced onion, green onions, and diced tomato to fish. toss gently to combine. Spoon about 3 tablespoons fish mixture into each lettuce leaf.'),
('4736', '1', 'Crust the salmon with the black sesame seeds and sprinkle with salt.'),
('4736', '2', 'Heat a nonstick pan over medium-high heat until it is very hot, and then add the oil, and the fish.  Sear 1 to 1 1/2 minutes per side, then remove to a plate to rest.'),
('4736', '3', 'While the fish rests, whisk together the lime juice, mirin, rice wine vinegar, soy sauce, and wasabi powder.'),
('4736', '4', 'Slice the fish into 1/2-inch slices.  Arrange the fish on a plate, and serve the sauce alongside.'),
('4736', '5', 'Garnish with a bunch of whole chives.'),
('4740', '1', 'Grate 1/2 teaspoon peel from lime and squeeze 1 teaspoon juice.  Stir together sour cream, lime peel, lime juice, 1/2 teaspoon cumin, sugar, 1/8 teaspoon salt and pepper in small bowl.  Set Lime Sauce aside.'),
('4740', '2', 'Rinse and pat dry salmon.  Sprinkle flesh side with remaining 1 teaspoon cumin and remaining 1/8 teaspoon salt.'),
('4740', '3', 'Heat oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('4740', '4', 'Add fillet, skin-side down, and cook 4 minutes.  Carefully turn fillet.  Continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes more or until fish flakes easily with fork (145F).'),
('4740', '5', 'Cut fillet into 4 pieces.'),
('4740', '6', 'Serve with Lime Sauce on top or on side of salmon.'),
('4742', '1', 'Rub sheet pan with the 2 teaspoons of oil and place side of salmon in pan. Salt and pepper salmon. Set aside.'),
('4742', '2', 'Add coriander, fennel seed, cumin seed, star anise, onion powder, garlic powder and cayenne pepper to a blender. Turn blender on high and process until whole spices become powder. With blender running, pour in 1/3 cup canola oil and blend until well combined. Stop blender to brush down sides of container, if necessary.'),
('4742', '3', 'Brush salmon with spice mixture. Allow salmon to sit at room temperature for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to the high broiler setting.'),
('4742', '4', 'Place salmon in the oven 6-inches from broiler. Cook until salmon reaches an internal temperature of 131 degrees F. This will take approximately 15 minutes, but will vary with different ovens.'),
('4742', '5', 'Remove from oven and let rest for 10 minutes, and then serve immediately. Note that the internal temperature of the fish will a rise a little as carry-over cooking occurs..'),
('4744', '1', 'Prepare grill.'),
('4744', '2', 'To prepare fish, sprinkle fillets evenly with garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Cover and refrigerate 15 minutes.'),
('4744', '3', 'To prepare glaze, combine nectar and next 6 ingredients (through 1/4 teaspoon pepper) in a small saucepan. bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer until reduced to 1/4 cup (about 10 minutes).'),
('4744', '4', 'Remove from heat. set aside.'),
('4744', '5', 'Place fillets, skin side up, on a grill rack coated with cooking spray. Grill 2 minutes. carefully turn over, and grill 4 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4744', '6', 'Brush each fillet with 1 tablespoon glaze. grill 30 seconds.'),
('4745', '1', 'To prepare salmon, heat a grill pan over medium-high heat.'),
('4745', '2', 'Combine first 5 ingredients. rub evenly over fillets. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('4745', '3', 'Add fillets to pan. cook 4 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4745', '4', 'While fish cooks, prepare salsa.'),
('4745', '5', 'Combine bell pepper and remaining ingredients.'),
('4745', '6', 'Serve salsa with fillets.'),
('4746', '1', 'Sprinkle fillets evenly with salt and pepper.'),
('4746', '2', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('4746', '3', 'Add fillets. cook 2 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4746', '4', 'Remove from pan.'),
('4746', '5', 'Recoat pan with cooking spray.'),
('4746', '6', 'Add shallots. saut 30 seconds. Stir in wine and rosemary. cook 30 seconds or until liquid almost evaporates.'),
('4746', '7', 'Add juice and syrup. bring to a boil, and cook 1 minute. Return fillets to pan. cook 1 minute on each side or until thoroughly heated.'),
('4746', '8', 'Seasoned haricots verts: Cook 1 pound haricots verts in boiling water 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),
('4746', '9', 'Drain. rinse with cold water. Pat dry.'),
('4746', '10', 'Combine with 1/3 cup chopped roasted red bell pepper and 1/4 cup toasted pine nuts.'),
('4746', '11', 'Combine 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar, 1/8 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, and 1/8 teaspoon dry mustard. Toss with bean mixture.'),
('4747', '1', 'To prepare sauce, combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl. set aside.'),
('4747', '2', 'To prepare fish, heat a nonstick grill pan over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Sprinkle fish evenly with salt and pepper. add fish to pan. Cover and grill 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4747', '3', 'Serve with sauce.'),
('4748', '1', 'Prepare grill.'),
('4748', '2', 'Place chiles on grill rack coated with cooking spray. grill 5 minutes on each side or until blackened.'),
('4748', '3', 'Place chiles in a heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag. seal.'),
('4748', '4', 'Let stand 5 minutes. Peel chiles. cut in half lengthwise. Discard seeds and membranes.'),
('4748', '5', 'Cut chiles into 1/4-inch strips.'),
('4748', '6', 'Place corn on grill rack coated with cooking spray. grill 10 minutes or until lightly browned, turning occasionally. Cool slightly.'),
('4748', '7', 'Cut kernels from cobs.'),
('4748', '8', 'Combine chiles, corn, tomato, cilantro, and juice. toss gently.'),
('4748', '9', 'Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper.'),
('4748', '10', 'Combine remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt, remaining 1/4 teaspoon black pepper, and cumin, stirring well. Rub spice mixture evenly over both sides of salmon.'),
('4748', '11', 'Place salmon on grill rack coated with cooking spray. grill 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4748', '12', 'Serve with relish.'),
('4749', '1', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl.'),
('4749', '2', 'Add 1/4 teaspoon salt. stir well. Cover and chill 30 minutes.'),
('4749', '3', 'Prepare grill.'),
('4749', '4', 'Sprinkle fish with remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.'),
('4749', '5', 'Place fish, skin side up, on grill rack coated with cooking spray. grill 3 minutes. Rotate fish one quarter-turn (45 degrees) for diamond-shaped crosshatches. Grill 3 minutes. Turn fish over. grill 4 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4749', '6', 'Serve with sauce and dill sprigs, if desired.'),
('4752', '1', 'Center an 18- by 28-inch piece of foil (or overlap two 12-inch-wide pieces) in a 14- by 17-inch baking pan. Rinse banana leaf and pat dry. center lengthwise on foil. Rinse fish and pat dry. rub your fingers over the flesh to find any bones, pull out with tweezers, and discard. Center fillet lengthwise, skin down, on leaf.'),
('4752', '2', 'Mix the cilantro, thyme, and oregano. In a bowl, mix half the herb mixture with crab, mayonnaise, and mustard.'),
('4752', '3', 'Spread evenly over salmon. Rinse and dry bowl.'),
('4752', '4', 'Rinse squash and bell pepper. Trim and discard stems from squash. stem and seed pepper.'),
('4752', '5', 'Cut vegetables into matchstick-size strips (about 3 in. long). Put vegetables, wine, olive oil, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and rest of herbs in bowl and mix to coat.'),
('4752', '6', 'Spread vegetable mixture over crab layer. Bring long sides of foil together over fish, wrapping banana leaf partially around fish, then fold in ends to seal.'),
('4752', '7', 'Bake in a 450 regular or convection oven until fish reaches 140 in center of thickest part (insert thermometer through foil and vegetable and crab layers to test), 20 to 25 minutes.'),
('4752', '8', 'Transfer packet to a platter and unwrap to serve. or, if desired, with two wide spatulas, carefully transfer leaf and fish from foil to platter.'),
('4752', '9', 'Add salt and pepper to taste.'),
('4752', '10', 'Cut fish into portions. slip a spatula between skin and fillet and lift off portions, leaving skin behind.'),
('4753', '1', 'In a medium bowl, toss the bok choy and pineapple with the cilantro, 3 tablespoons of the oil,  teaspoon salt, and  teaspoon pepper.');